[[File:Shengzhou Bamboo Weaving Basket in Zhejiang Provincial Museum 2014-04.JPG|thumb|Shaoxing octagonal three grid bamboo baskets from [[Shengzhou]] (1950's)]]
[[File:China from the Eyes of the Flying Tigers 1944-1945 54.jpg|thumb|Chinese boy carrying a bamboo basket (before 1945)]]
[[File:Basket making in Hainan - 01.jpg|thumb|Bamboo basket maker in Hainan]]
'''Bamboo weaving''' is a form of [[bambooworking]] and a [[craft]] of [[China]]. It involves manipulating bamboo into various traditional knit and woven patterns to create both useful and decorative objects. 

==History==
Woven bamboo goods with an age of up to 7000 years unearthed at the [[Hemudu]] cultural ruins show that bamboo weaving has been a part of Chinese cultural history since very early periods of development.<ref name="chinascenic.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.chinascenic.com/magazine/the-world-of-bamboo-212.html|title=Magazine - China Scenic|website=Chinascenic.com|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref> By the [[Warring States period]], technique had substantially improved and examples of many types of bamboo wares have been found, such as boxes and bowls.{{Citation needed |date=October 2017}}  During the [[Qin Dynasty|Qin]] and [[Han Dynasty|Han]] dynasties these techniques were applied to create new types of bamboo wares such as mats and curtains.{{Citation needed |date=October 2017}}  A notable example from this period would be bamboo weaving patterns represented in bronze from a chariot found in the [[Mausoleum of the First Qin Emperor|mausoleum]] of [[Qin Shi Huang]]{{Citation needed |date=October 2017}}.  

By the [[Tang Dynasty|Tang]] and [[Song Dynasty|Song]] dynasties, bamboo weaving had expanded beyond practical objects and into creation of toys.{{Citation needed |date=October 2017}}  During the middle [[Ming dynasty]], bamboo weaving was mostly used for boxes and storage containers.{{Citation needed |date=October 2017}}  

After the founding of the [[People's Republic of China]], efforts have been made by the government to encourage and preserve the cultural history and skill of bamboo weaving, awarding titles to particularly accomplished masters of the craft, as well as designating some regions as recognized for their long history of practicing the art.<ref name="chinascenic.com"/> 

[[Anji County]] is particularly important to the production of bamboo crafts due to both the great variety and quantity of bamboo grown, and a high concentration of history and expertise in bamboo crafts.<ref>https://www.cifor.org/library/419/the-role-of-bamboo-plantations-in-rural-development-the-case-of-anji-county-zhejiang-china/</ref><ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.jrurstud.2016.11.012 |title=Sustainability, space and supply chains: The role of bamboo in Anji County, China |journal=Journal of Rural Studies |volume=49 |pages=128–39 |year=2017 |last1=Flynn |first1=Andrew |last2=Chan |first2=Kin Wing |last3=Zhu |first3=Zhao Hua |last4=Yu |first4=Li }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1059430.shtml|title=Craftsmen make bamboo products in E China's county - Global Times|first=Global|last=Times|website=Globaltimes.cn|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.sina.com/news/2017-08-02/detail-ifyiswpt4973952.shtml|title=Craftsmen make bamboo products in E China's county  - Life & Culture News - SINA English|website=English.sina.com|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref name="chinascenic.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wap.chinadaily.com.cn/2016-11/18/content_27414632.htm|title=Young entrepreneur eager to revive bamboo culture|website=Wap.chinadaily.com.cn|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref>

==Applications==
Bamboo weaving in contemporary China is mainly used for household objects, such as furniture, tea sets, curtains, and lanterns. 

