===Life expectancy at birth=== :Total population: 70.2 years :Male: 68.8 years :Female: 71.7 years (2017<ref name="cia.gov"/> est.) Life expectancy at birth is 70.2 years, which is an increase from 66.3 years in 2005. Women with 71.7 years lived longer than men (68.8).
Prime Minister [[Tshering Tobgay]] said that the good news is life expectancy has crossed 70 years.<ref> KuenselOnline [http://www.kuenselonline.com/bhutans-population-is-735553/]</ref> ===Vital statistics=== Below is a table of Bhutan vital statistics since 1950 published by the [[United Nations]] [[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs|Department of Economic and Social Affairs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/unpp/Panel_profiles.htm |title=Bhutan: Demographic Profile, Medium Variant 1950–2100 |work=World Population Prospects: The 2010 Revision |publisher=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Population Division, Population Projections and Estimates Section |accessdate=2011-10-30}} (entry: ''Bhutan'')</ref>
