{{Orphan|date=February 2016}}
{{unreferenced|date=December 2016}}

'''Kathariya Rajput'''/'''Katariya Jat'''/'''Kataria Thakurs''' or simply '''Katara''' are a [[Rajput]] patrilineal clan of the [[Indian subcontinent]]. They rose to prominence from the late 8th century CE, and, until the 17th century, designated as excellent [[Bladesmith]]s and first to use [[wootz steel]] in [[South Asia]] for swords, they dominated many regions of central and northern India, especially the regions of present-day [[Punjab, Pakistan]].

The Katara Rajput population although very scarce are found spread through much of the [[subcontinent]], particularly in North, West and Central India. These areas include [[Rajasthan]], [[Haryana]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] and [[Gujarat]].

